# Completion and Quality

## Marking work completed

- Do not mark a task or phase completed until the test suite passes. Run tests (e.g. `npm test` or `pnpm test`) and fix any failures before updating todos or calling the work done.
- If the project has no tests yet for the changed area, add or extend tests for critical behavior, then run the suite before marking complete.

## Code style

- Do not add emojis in code, commit messages, or docs unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- Avoid unnecessary comments. Prefer clear names and small functions. Comment only when explaining non-obvious business logic or constraints.

## Critical features

- Payment, checkout, order creation, and auth flows must have tests (unit and/or integration) where feasible. Sanitization, validation, and deposit calculation must be covered by tests.
